      "content": "that makes sense. so when we talk about those \"evolutionary leaps\" and the shift towards modern systems, are there specific types of cultures or regions that historically represented these \"primitive\" stages before they transitioned into more complex civilizations? like, can you give some examples of groups that served as the baseline for these earlier social structures?",
