      "content": "Historically, many indigenous groups in various parts of the world fit the description of simpler, pre-modern social structures. For instance, some nomadic hunter-gatherer tribes or early agricultural communities in Africa and Oceania represent these baseline societies. These groups often maintained smaller, more tightly knit social units with less formalized governance compared to the established empires of the Old World. Their existence showcases a different, often less technologically driven, mode of human social organization.",
